summary: COLLAGE ARTIST TRADING CARD Gravity Deprivation Kornelia Hoffmann's collage Schwindel der Freiheit (Dizziness of Freedom) #3 is...
caption:
COLLAGE ARTIST TRADING CARD

Gravity Deprivation

Kornelia Hoffmann’s collage Schwindel der Freiheit (Dizziness of Freedom) #3 is featured in Collage Artist Trading Cards Pack 8. She writes, “My works deal with spaces, room conditions, their emotional meanings and their impressions on the body. Architecture and habitats as body sensations and their effect on the organism, such as dizziness, gravity deprivation, well-being, feeling “at home”–memories, experiences and visions. With the help of the collage/montage as an artistic strategy, I arrange found material and my own photographs of houses, residential spaces and urban structures into new compositions and connections.” MORE

Kolaj #24 is now available. Our goal with every printed issue is that Kolaj Magazine is essential reading for anyone interested in the role of contemporary collage in art, culture, and society. Kolaj #24 is no different.

Are you getting Kolaj Magazine delivered to your door? Subscribe Today!

blog.description: Mighty/Gaby| She/her | 18 | ❤️Feb 19❤️ | Comic Artist and Writer | OCs? To Mnay to Count | Fandoms? Mega Man, Cuphead, Miraculous Lady Bug, Rwby, Splatoon, Smash Bros, etc. | Original Series: Celestial Guardians, Lost Between the Pages, and Eternal Curse of the Nutcracker, My Brother, the Merman | Fan Series: Mega Man Harmony |

summary: 2019 is a Big Year, Here are my Plans.
title: 2019 is a Big Year, Here are my Plans.
body:
Hello everyone! 2019 is a big year in my life, I’m going off to college soon, I’m almost an adult, I’ve got lots of projects in the works! So to start of the year I’d like to share the projects I’m working on.

1. Celestial Guardians

Synopsis: Celestial Guardians are specially selected beings who travel from universe to universe defending the order of time and space from criminals attempting to change fate or use dimensional travel for their own personal gain. This comic follows Jacie and her other newly selected friends as they learn to control their powers and fight to protect the multiverse.

Guardians is my passion project, an original comic that I’ve been trying to start since freshman year. I’m working on scripts and I’m really excited to finally post something for Guardians! Here’s an updated ref on one of the main characters. I’ll be posting more refs and sketches for guardians on this blog in the future.


2. Eternal Curse of the Nutcracker

Synopsis: It’s a traditional Christmas story, the Nutcracker saves the day and breaks his curse with the help of a kind girl. The only thing about this particular story…… it’s 100% true and the curse as well as the dreaded mouse king reappear every 10 years. Now, at the dawn of the 20th incarnation two friends, Darren and Carla, find themselves roped into the classic tale.  Will they be able to endure it? Especially against a foe with a plan that nearly 200 years in the making?

This one is a team effort with some friends on discord and I’m having an absolute blast working on it. This one might begin closer to the holiday season but I will keep this one up to date with concept sketches too!


3. Lost Between the Pages

Synopsis: Lynn is a young woman who has finally reached a point in her life where she can leave home and find herself. It’s certainly a difficult task, especially for someone who’s only a few inches tall. Along her adventures she’ll make new friends as well as new enemies while adjusting to life in a great big world.

This one is a cute slice of life comic that I’ve actually drew a few pages for! This one is prolly the comic that’s closest to being ready to post. For now here’s a little glimpse to the comic.

4. ONLINE STORE!!!!

IM SUPER EXCITED FOR THIS ONE FOLKS! I hade to make products to sell for a school art festival and my friends and I made smash bros keychains and I decided to open up a storeenvy this year! I’m still finalizing things so expect this store to open mid February. If your a smash fan or if you want your oc as a key chain then plz check the shop out when it’s open! Here are the keychains I drew  for the festival.


Thanks again for your time, if your interested in any of these projects, firstly, thanks so much it means the world, secondly, stay tuned on this blog for future updates on all the projects.
